            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>NormxNormNegx</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>NormxNormNegx</caption>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>If <math>
                     <latex>x\geq 0</latex>
                  </math>, then <math>
                     <latex>-x\leq 0</latex>
                  </math>, and so</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>NormDifference</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>NormDifference</caption>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>This follows from the previous part by observing that <math>
                     <latex>x-y = (-1)(y-x)</latex>
                  </math>, and so</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>NormProduct</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>NormProduct</caption>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>The key is to treat the case where <math>
                     <latex>0\leq x,y</latex>
                  </math>. We then have <math>
                     <latex>\Abs{x} = x</latex>
                  </math> and <math>
                     <latex>\Abs{y}=y</latex>
                  </math> and, further,</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>NormRatio</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>NormRatio</caption>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>This follows from the previous part by recalling the definition <math>
                     <latex>\frac{x}{y} = x\cdot y^{-1}</latex>
                  </math>.</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>Comparison</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>Comparison</caption>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>If <math>
                     <latex>0\leq x</latex>
                  </math>, then <math>
                     <latex>x=\Abs{x}</latex>
                  </math>. On the other hand, if <math>
                     <latex>x\leq 0</latex>
                  </math>, then <math>
                     <latex>0\leq -x=\Abs{x}</latex>
                  </math> and so</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
